CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 5, 1974, pg. 26, reads: "'Butch' Martin: Pittsburgh Music Man - Martin, Watson and Company - Butch Martin, seated at the piano, delivers an impromptu version of an original composition. Martin's Pittsburgh based company, Sonic Records seems a sure bet for future success."
TitMainTitle: Joane Sandy West singing, with her godfather Butch Martin on piano, and Billy Watson on guitar, in Martin's dining room of home on Paulson Avenue, East Liberty, another version
